trans-unit.source: Handle the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.Navigated?displayProperty=fullName> event to receive notification when the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser> control has navigated to a new document.

The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowserNavigatedEventArgs> object passed to the event handler lets you retrieve the location of the new document through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowserNavigatedEventArgs.Url%2A> property.

When the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.Navigated?displayProperty=fullName> event occurs, the new document has begun loading, which means you can access some of its content through the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.Document%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentText%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser.DocumentStream%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowserNavigatedEventArgs"></xref> class.
A <xref href="System.Uri"></xref> representing the location of the document to which the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser"></xref> control has navigated.
Gets the location of the document to which the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser"></xref> control has navigated.
A <xref href="System.Uri"></xref> representing the location of the document to which the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.WebBrowser"></xref> control has navigated.
